Named for one of the [[Elf-Kings|The Elf-Kings]], [[King Lyrin]], Lyrin Bay is a bay on the west coast of [[Eudin|The Kingdom of Eudin]]. It is known for its shear rock cliffs, standing upwards of 300 metres tall in some locations. The bay is reletively sheltered from ocean weather by a line of large sea stacks and arches near its mouth. The city of [[Calhun]] is the most important settlement that sits on Lyrin bay.